[
    {
        "content": "<p>For a category C and for each object X of C, we can form the poset Sub(X) of subobjects of X as in <a href=\"https://ncatlab.org/nlab/show/subobject\">nlab</a></p>",
        "id": 253350012,
        "sender_full_name": "Jade Master",
        "timestamp": 1631669909
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I'm wondering what conditions on C make Sub(X) a boolean algebra?</p>",
        "id": 253350035,
        "sender_full_name": "Jade Master",
        "timestamp": 1631669934
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>The top element should be 1_X and if C has an initial object 0, then the map 0 -&gt; X becomes the bottom element.</p>",
        "id": 253350214,
        "sender_full_name": "Jade Master",
        "timestamp": 1631670069
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>If C has pullbacks and pushouts then you get unions and intersections. The one I'm struggling with is negation.</p>",
        "id": 253350303,
        "sender_full_name": "Jade Master",
        "timestamp": 1631670139
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>A negation of a subobject <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>A</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">A</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">A</span></span></span></span> is a subobject <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">¬</mi><mi>A</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\neg A</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">¬</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">A</span></span></span></span> with <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>A</mi><mo>∩</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">¬</mi><mi>A</mi><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">⊥</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">A \\cap \\neg A = \\bot</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">A</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222222222222222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">∩</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222222222222222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">¬</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">A</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.69444em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">⊥</span></span></span></span> and <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>A</mi><mo>∪</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">¬</mi><mi>A</mi><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">⊤</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">A \\cup \\neg A = \\top</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">A</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222222222222222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">∪</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222222222222222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">¬</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">A</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.69444em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">⊤</span></span></span></span></p>",
        "id": 253350621,
        "sender_full_name": "Jade Master",
        "timestamp": 1631670411
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Have you read about <a href=\"https://ncatlab.org/nlab/show/Heyting+category\">Heyting categories</a> and <a href=\"https://ncatlab.org/nlab/show/Boolean+category\">Boolean categories</a>?</p>",
        "id": 253354047,
        "sender_full_name": "Mike Shulman",
        "timestamp": 1631673311
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"276037\">Jade Master</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/229199-learning.3A-questions/topic/When.20are.20subobjects.20nice.3F/near/253350035\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>I'm wondering what conditions on C make Sub(X) a boolean algebra?</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>In an elementary topos,  one condition that implies boolean is well-pointed: for f, g : A --&gt; B, if fa = ga for all a : 1 --&gt; A, then f = g.</p>",
        "id": 253356397,
        "sender_full_name": "Steve Awodey",
        "timestamp": 1631675559
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"276037\">Jade Master</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/229199-learning.3A-questions/topic/When.20are.20subobjects.20nice.3F/near/253350303\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>If C has pullbacks and pushouts then you get unions and intersections. The one I'm struggling with is negation.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>No, this is more subtle than you are making it out to be. The unique morphism from the initial object may fail to be a monomorphism. Pushouts of monos may not be mono. etc.</p>",
        "id": 253357307,
        "sender_full_name": "Zhen Lin Low",
        "timestamp": 1631676551
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"276777\">@Mike Shulman</span> Oh cool. Im looking for boolean categories I think then.</p>",
